                  "elements": [
                    {
                      "id": "9abb326",
                      "elType": "widget",
                      "settings": {
                        "editor": "<p>The success of this project lies in meticulous design and the seamless coordination of natural elements. Terracing, a monumental task, is protected by ground cover, shielding the land from erosion. Contour line and Keyline Design principles optimize soil movement and slow rainfall impact. Vetiver, acting as a steadfast anchor, preserves soil integrity, allowing the lush bamboo canopy to flourish.</p><p>As the bamboo canopy matures, it captures sunlight, gradually shading out Vetiver. This natural progression makes Vetiver an ideal tool for transitioning from intensive agriculture to a climax forest, where the ecosystem can thrive independently. It is a choreography of regeneration, where each element plays its role, and nature herself applauds the performance.</p>",
                        "align": "justify",
                        "typography_typography": "custom",
                        "typography_font_weight": "400",
                        "typography_line_height": {
